                  "fill": "$text-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "This is a strong plan with clear phase separation and appropriate parallelism in Phase 2.\n\nThe migration approach — replacing SessionToken with ComplianceToken while maintaining backwards compatibility — is the safest path for compliance. The phased rollout ensures we can validate each step before proceeding.\n\nI recommend adding a feature flag (e.g. compliance_token_v2) so the migration can be rolled back quickly if the new HMAC-SHA256 hashing causes unexpected latency or validation failures in production.\n\nThe QA checkpoint between Phase 2 and Phase 3 is essential — Kai should verify that both old and new token formats are accepted during the grace period.\n\nOverall: well-structured, low risk, appropriate model assignments.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.6,
                  "fontFamily": "$font-ui",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
